          </span>
          <span class="text-slate-700">&middot;</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-emerald-400/70">Updated April 18, 2026</span>
          <span class="text-slate-700">&middot;</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-600">Pedro Nunes</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
          Before Your Agent Calls an API at 3am: A Reliability Checklist
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          A practical pre-flight checklist for the failure modes that actually matter once an autonomous agent is allowed to call a live API unattended.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose-rhumb" set:html={htmlContent} />

      <section class="mt-16 rounded-[28px] border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5 p-8 text-center sm:text-left">
        <div class="text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-emerald-300 mb-3">Next honest step</div>
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
          Turn the checklist into one bounded execution lane
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto sm:mx-0">
          If the checklist already tells you the workflow needs tighter authority and clearer recovery paths, move into capability-first onboarding or the direct managed path instead of wiring a giant connector list.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:justify-start">
          <a
            href="/blog/capability-first-agent-onboarding?rhumb_experiment=e004&rhumb_source=reliability-checklist-onboarding"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-emerald-400 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-display font-semibold text-navy hover:bg-emerald-300 transition-colors duration-200"
          >
            See the capability-first handoff &rarr;
          </a>
          <a
            href="/start-managed-execution?rhumb_experiment=e004&rhumb_source=reliability-checklist-direct"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/30 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-display font-semibold text-emerald-200 hover:border-emerald-400/60 hover:text-emerald-100 transition-colors duration-200"
          >
            Open the managed path &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-slate-100 mb-4">
          Related
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a
            href="/blog/how-to-evaluate-apis-for-agents"
            class="block bg-surface border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-amber/30 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
              Methodology
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
              How to Evaluate APIs for AI Agents
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">
              The broader framework behind these five questions, with the structural dimensions Rhumb scores across every API.
            </p>
          </a>
          <a
            href="/blog/securing-keys-for-agents"
            class="block bg-surface border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-amber/30 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
              Credential Path
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
              How to Secure Your API Keys for Agent Use
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">
              The practical credential patterns that keep bounded execution live after the first demo.
            </p>
          </a>
          <a
            href="/blog/twilio-api-autopsy"
            class="block bg-surface border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-amber/30 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
